Saudi Arabia Awards Water Contracts Worth $43 Million, SPA Says

-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 
2011-04-23T12:04:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/saudi-arabia-awards-water-contracts-worth-43-million-spa-says.html
Saudi Arabia  awarded contracts
worth 161 million riyals ($43 million) to develop water and
sanitation projects in the kingdom, the official  Saudi Press
Agency  reported, citing Minister of Water and Electricity
Abdullah al-Hussayen.  The contracts include digging wells, water pipelines and
new sanitation systems, the Riyadh-based news service reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  